"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The DateFormatter and MonthLocator are being used together but the DateFormatter will override any formatting done by the MonthLocator. The MonthLocator is used to specify the locations of the ticks, but then DateFormatter is used to format all the ticks as year-month. If the intention is to show every month, then the DateFormatter should be used with the MonthLocator to specify the interval between the dates to be shown.\",\n  \"patch\": \"19c19\\n<ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(MonthLocator())\\n---\\n>ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(MonthLocator(interval=1))\\n\"\n}"